{"title_page": "Namitha Pramod", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Namitha Pramod\n| image              = Namita Pramod 1.jpg\n| caption            = Namitha Pramod in 2014\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1996|09|19|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ibtimes.co.in/namitha-pramod-turns-19-rare-unseen-photos-amar-akbar-anthony-actress-photos-647139|title=Namitha Pramod turns 19|agency=m.ibtimes.co.in|date=18 September 2015}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Thiruvananthapuram]], Kerala, India\n| education          = [[St. Teresa's College]]\n| occupation         = [[Actress]]\n| parents            = \n| years_active       = 2007\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Namitha Pramod''' (born 19 September 1996) is an Indian film actress, who appears predominantly in [[Cinema of Kerala|Malayalam]] films alongside a few [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] and [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] films.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/314694/ |title=\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d46 \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d2a\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24 \u0d24\u0d3e\u0d2e\u0d30, Interview \u2013 Mathrubhumi Movies |publisher=Mathrubhumi.com |date=5 November 2012 |accessdate=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107004629/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/314694/ |archivedate=7 January 2014  }}</ref> She made her acting debut in the Malayalam film ''[[Traffic (2011 film)|Traffic]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/malayalamContentView.do?contentId=14702056&programId=1073752204&channelId=-1073750705&BV_ID=@@@&tabId=3 |title=Movies &#124; Interviews &#124; |publisher=Manorama Online |date= |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nNamitha was born in [[Thiruvananthapuram]] as the daughter of Pramod, a businessman and Indu, a housewife.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/130818/entertainment-mollywood/article/namitha-pramod-shooting-star |title=Namitha Pramod: A shooting star |publisher=Deccan Chronicle |date=18 August 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> She has a younger sister Akhita Pramod.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/article/84096.html |title=Namitha, into the big league |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=25 July 2012 |accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref> She did her schooling at Carmel Girls Higher Secondary School in [[Thiruvananthapuram]].<ref name=\"thehindu1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/role-call/article3947245.ece |title=Role call |newspaper=The Hindu |date=29 September 2012 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> She was enrolled at the [[St. Teresa's College]] to pursue a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA degree]] in Sociology in June 2014.<ref>Nicy V.P (25 June 2014). [http://www.ibtimes.co.in/interview-i-want-be-teacher-says-namitha-pramod-602989 \"Interview: 'I Want to Be a Teacher', says Namitha Pramod\"]. ''IB Times''. Retrieved 22 February 2015.</ref> She has stated that she was \"not going to let [her] acting career compromise [her] studies\".<ref name=\"deccan 40703\">[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140703/entertainment-mollywood/article/namitha-pramods-dream-working-prithviraj-comes-true Namitha Pramod's dream of working with Prithviraj comes true]. Deccanchronicle.com (3 July 2014). Retrieved on 14 Octogenarian 2015.</ref>\n\n==Career==\nNamitha started acting when she was in seventh standard by taking on roles in serials such as ''Vellankanni Mathavu'' where she played the role of Mathavu, ''Amme Devi'' where she played the role of Devi and ''Ente Manasa Puthri'' where she played Anjali.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20120711035442/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/kochi/namitha-pramod-plays-fisherwoman-503 Namitha Pramod plays a fisherwoman | Deccan Chronicle]. Web.archive.org (11 July 2012). Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/65293 |title=\u0d38\u0d3e\u0d27\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d23 \u0d1c\u0d40\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d4d \u0d07\u0d37\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d02 |publisher=mangalam.com |date=11 June 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> She made her debut in films when she acted as Riya, the dying daughter of Rahman and Lena, in [[Rajesh Pillai]]'s critically acclaimed ''[[Traffic (2011 film)|Traffic]]''.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\"/> In her next film ''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]'' she played her first lead role, playing a fisherwoman, opposite [[Nivin Pauly]].<ref name=\"thehindu1\"/> It was followed by more lead roles in ''[[Sound Thoma]]'' with [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]] and ''[[Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum]]'' with [[Kunchacko Boban]] in which she played a [[Mohiniyattam]] dancer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/354791/ |title=\u0d28\u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d24 \u0d31\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d4d\u200c\u0d38\u0d4d\u200c, Interview \u2013 Mathrubhumi Movies |publisher=Mathrubhumi.com |date=18 April 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024234532/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/354791/ |archivedate=24 October 2014  }}</ref> She was not trained in Mohiniyattam and learned the dance steps in [[Saranya Mohan]]'s dance school in [[Alappuzha]] for four days.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle1\"/> Both films were successful and she was selected as Top Star (Female) 2013 in Malayalam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themoviesdetails.blogspot.in/2014/01/top-10-highest-grossing-malayalam.html |title=The Movies Details/Reviews: TOP 10 HIGHEST GROSSING MALAYALAM MOVIES \u22122013 |publisher=Themoviesdetails.blogspot.in |date=9 January 2014 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, she was first seen in ''En Kadhal Pudhithu'', her debut Tamil film directed by Maaris Kumar which had a delayed release,<ref>[http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/130307/entertainment-kollywood/article/trailing-his-mentor Trailing his mentor | Deccan Chronicle]. Archives.deccanchronicle.com (7 March 2013). Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref> followed by Lijin Jose's ''[[Law Point]]'' in which she played a modern, city bred girl named Maya.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/malayalam/news-and-interviews/Namitha-going-glam/articleshow/27155306.cms |title=Namitha going glam \u2013 The Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=10 December 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mangalam.com/women/interview/16184 |title=\u0d28\u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d3e \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d2e\u0d4b\u0d26\u0d4d\u200c.. |publisher=mangalam.com |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> In [[Lal Jose]]'s ''[[Vikramadithyan]]'', she played the role of Deepika, a [[Konkani]] girl, which required her to speak a few lines in [[Konkani language|Konkani]], a language she had never used before. Her next film ''Villali Veeran'', in which she paired once again with Dileep, had her playing the role of an ad filmmaker.<ref>Nambidi, Parvathy. (26 June 2014) [http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/Veeran-Set-for-Onam-Arrival/2014/06/26/article2300320.ece 'Veeran' Set for Onam Arrival]. The New Indian Express. Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref> Her last release in 2014 was ''Ormayundo Ee Mukham'', a romantic drama in which she was cast opposite [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]].Her first release of 2015 was [[Chandrettan Evideya]] where she portrayed the role of Dr.Geethanjali along with [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]] and [[Anusree]].Her performance was critically acclaim and she went on to receive her first nomination at [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Malayalam|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress]]. Her next released Malayalam movie [[Amar Akbar Anthony (2015 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]] starring Prithviraj, Jayasurya and Indrajith directed by popular stage artist Nadirshah where she played a role as a dancer was a blockbuster hit in Malayalam theatres. Her latest movie with [[Dhyan Sreenivasan]] was [[Adi Kapyare Kootamani]] directed by debutant John Varghese.The movie was declared superhit.\n\nShe has acted in many [[commercials]] of [[Bhima Jewellers]], Francis Alukkas and Ripple Tea. She has participated in the popular [[reality show]] ''[[Ningalkkum Aakaam Kodeeshwaran]]'' on [[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Language\n!co-star\n! class=\"wikitable sortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Traffic (2011 film)|Traffic]]'' || Riya || [[Malayalam]] || [[Kunchako Boban]]||Debut\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]'' || Thamara || [[Malayalam]] || [[Nivin Pauly]]||\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2013 || ''[[Sound Thoma]]'' || Sreelakshmi || [[Malayalam]] || [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]]||\n|-\n| ''[[Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum]]'' || Kainakari Jayasree || [[Malayalam]] || [[Kunchako Boban]]||\n|-\n| rowspan=5| 2014 || ''En Kaadhal Pudhithu'' || Nandini || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Law Point]]'' || Maya || [[Malayalam]] ||[[Kunchako Boban]]||\n|-\n| ''[[Vikramadithyan]]'' || Deepika Pai||   [[Malayalam]] || [[Dulquer Salmaan]]   ||\n|-\n| ''[[Villali Veeran]]'' || Narmada || [[Malayalam]] || [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]]||\n|-\n| ''[[Ormayundo Ee Mukham]]'' || Nitya  || [[Malayalam]] || [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]]||\n|-\n| rowspan=3| 2015 || ''[[Chandrettan Evideya]]'' || Dr. Geethanjali/ Vasanthamallika\n||[[Malayalam]] || [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[Amar Akbar Anthony (2015 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]]'' || Jennie ||   [[Malayalam]] || [[Jayasurya]] [[Prithviraj Sukumaran|Prithviraj]] [[Indrajith Sukumaran|Indrajith]]||\n|-\n| ''[[Adi Kapyare Kootamani]]'' || Adhishta Lekshmi ||[[Malayalam]] || [[Dhyan Sreenivasan]]||\n|-\n| 2016||''[[Chuttalabbai]]'' ||Kavya ||    [[Telugu language|Telugu]] || [[Aadi (actor)|Aadi]]||\n|-\n| rowspan =2|2017||    ''[[Role Models (2017 film)|Role Models]]|| Shreya||  [[Malayalam]]|| [[Fahadh Faasil]]||\n|-\n|''[[Kathalo Rajakumari]]'' ||Sita || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] || [[Nara Rohit]]||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018|| ''[[Nimir]]'' || Malar || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] || [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]]||\n|-\n|''[[Kammara Sambhavam]]''|| Bhanumathy||[[Malayalam]]|| [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]]||\n|-\n|Rowspan=1|2019\n|''[[Margamkali (film)|Margamkali]]''||Urmila||[[Malayalam]]||Bibin George||\n|-\n|2020||''[[Al Mallu]]''||Nayana||[[Malayalam]]||[[Miya George]]||\n|-\n|TBA||''[[Professor Dinkan]]''|| ||[[Malayalam]]||[[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]]|| Filming  \n|}\n\n==Television serials==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year!!Serial !! Role !! Channel\n|-\n|2008-2010||''Ente Manasaputhri'' || Anjali ||[[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]]\n|-\n|2008||''Ulladakkam''||Cameo in Title Song||[[Amrita TV]]\n|-\n|2007||''Vellankanni Mathavu'' || Mathavu ||[[Surya TV]]\n|-\n|2007|| ''Amme Devi'' || Devi ||[[Surya TV]]\n|-\n|2006||''Mylanchy Mazha''||Amina||[[Album|Music Album]]{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Film\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n|-\n||2013\n|  [[Amrita TV|Amrita Film Awards]]\n|New Face of the Year\n|''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]''\n|Thamara\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n||2013\n| [[2nd South Indian International Movie Awards]]\n| Best Female Debutant\n|''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]''\n|Thamara\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n||2014\n| [[Asianet Film Award]]\n| Popular Actress\n|''[[Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum]]''\n|Kainakari Jayasree\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metromatinee.com/news-articles/16th-ujala-asianet-film-awards-2014-winners-list-7548 |title=16th Ujala Asianet Film Awards 2014 \u2013 Winners List |publisher=Metromatinee.com |date=11 January 2014 |accessdate=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517014018/http://www.metromatinee.com/news-articles/16th-ujala-asianet-film-awards-2014-winners-list-7548 |archivedate=17 May 2014  }}</ref>\n|-\n||2014\n| [[Asianet Film Award]]\n| Best Actress\n|''[[Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum]]''\n|Kainakari Jayasree\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n||2015\n| [[Asianet Film Award]]\n| Best Star Pair\n|''[[Ormayundo Ee Mukham]]''\n| Nithya\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n||2015\n| [[Asianet Film Award]]\n| Best Character Actress\n|''[[Ormayundo Ee Mukham]]''\n|Nithya\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n||2015\n| [[Vanitha Film Awards]]\n| Best Star Pair\n|''[[Vikramadithyan]]''\n|Deepika\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n||2015\n| [[4th South Indian International Movie Awards]]\n| Best Actress \u2013 Malayalam\n|''[[Vikramadithyan]]''\n|Deepika\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|| 2016\n||[[Filmfare Awards]]\n||[[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Malayalam|Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Malayalam]]\n||''[[Chandrettan Evideya]]''\n|Dr.Geethanjali/Vasanthamallika\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n||2016\n| [[1st IIFA Utsavam]]\n| [[Best Supporting Actress]]\n|''[[Chandrettan Evideya]]''\n|Dr.Geethanjali/Vasanthamallika\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|| 2016\n||[[5th South Indian International Movie Awards]]\n||Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Malayalam\n||''[[Chandrettan Evideya]]''\n|Dr.Geethanjali/Vasanthamallika\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2016\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Vanitha Film Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Most Popular Actress\n| ''[[Amar Akbar Anthony (2015 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]]''\n| Jennie\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{won}}\n|-\n| ''[[Adi Kapyare Kootamani]]''\n| Adhista Lekshmi\n|-\n||2016\n| Anand TV Awards\n| Best Actress\n|''[[Chandrettan Evideya]]''\n|Dr.Geethanjali/Vasanthamallika\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Namitha Pramod}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=5166292}}\n* [https://www.myfashioncampus.com/2018/05/namitha-pramod-wiki-height-weight-age.html Namitha Pramod] on MFC\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pramod, Namitha}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Kottayam district]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Kerala]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam television]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Namitha Pramod\n| image              = Namita Pramod 1.jpg\n| caption            = Namitha Pramod in 2014\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1996|09|19|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ibtimes.co.in/namitha-pramod-turns-19-rare-unseen-photos-amar-akbar-anthony-actress-photos-647139|title=Namitha Pramod turns 19|agency=m.ibtimes.co.in|date=18 September 2015}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Thiruvananthapuram]], Kerala, India\n| education          = [[St. Teresa's College]]\n| occupation         = [[Actress]]\n| parents            = \n| years_active       = 2007\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Namitha Pramod''' (born 19 September 1996) is an Indian film actress, who appears predominantly in [[Cinema of Kerala|Malayalam]] films alongside a few [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] and [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] films.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/314694/ |title=\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d46 \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d2a\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24 \u0d24\u0d3e\u0d2e\u0d30, Interview \u2013 Mathrubhumi Movies |publisher=Mathrubhumi.com |date=5 November 2012 |accessdate=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107004629/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/314694/ |archivedate=7 January 2014  }}</ref> She made her acting debut in the Malayalam film ''[[Traffic (2011 film)|Traffic]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/malayalamContentView.do?contentId=14702056&programId=1073752204&channelId=-1073750705&BV_ID=@@@&tabId=3 |title=Movies &#124; Interviews &#124; |publisher=Manorama Online |date= |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nNamitha was born in [[Thiruvananthapuram]] as the daughter of Pramod, a businessman and Indu, a housewife.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/130818/entertainment-mollywood/article/namitha-pramod-shooting-star |title=Namitha Pramod: A shooting star |publisher=Deccan Chronicle |date=18 August 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> She has a younger sister Akhita Pramod.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/article/84096.html |title=Namitha, into the big league |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=25 July 2012 |accessdate=1 January 2013}}</ref> She did her schooling at Carmel Girls Higher Secondary School in [[Thiruvananthapuram]].<ref name=\"thehindu1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/role-call/article3947245.ece |title=Role call |newspaper=The Hindu |date=29 September 2012 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> She was enrolled at the [[St. Teresa's College]] to pursue a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA degree]] in Sociology in June 2014.<ref>Nicy V.P (25 June 2014). [http://www.ibtimes.co.in/interview-i-want-be-teacher-says-namitha-pramod-602989 \"Interview: 'I Want to Be a Teacher', says Namitha Pramod\"]. ''IB Times''. Retrieved 22 February 2015.</ref> She has stated that she was \"not going to let [her] acting career compromise [her] studies\".<ref name=\"deccan 40703\">[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140703/entertainment-mollywood/article/namitha-pramods-dream-working-prithviraj-comes-true Namitha Pramod's dream of working with Prithviraj comes true]. Deccanchronicle.com (3 July 2014). Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref>\n\n==Career==\nNamitha started acting when she was in seventh standard by taking on roles in serials such as ''Vellankanni Mathavu'' where she played the role of Mathavu, ''Amme Devi'' where she played the role of Devi and ''Ente Manasa Puthri'' where she played Anjali.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20120711035442/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/kochi/namitha-pramod-plays-fisherwoman-503 Namitha Pramod plays a fisherwoman | Deccan Chronicle]. Web.archive.org (11 July 2012). Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/65293 |title=\u0d38\u0d3e\u0d27\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d23 \u0d1c\u0d40\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d4d \u0d07\u0d37\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d02 |publisher=mangalam.com |date=11 June 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> She made her debut in films when she acted as Riya, the dying daughter of Rahman and Lena, in [[Rajesh Pillai]]'s critically acclaimed ''[[Traffic (2011 film)|Traffic]]''.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\"/> In her next film ''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]'' she played her first lead role, playing a fisherwoman, opposite [[Nivin Pauly]].<ref name=\"thehindu1\"/> It was followed by more lead roles in ''[[Sound Thoma]]'' with [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]] and ''[[Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum]]'' with [[Kunchacko Boban]] in which she played a [[Mohiniyattam]] dancer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/354791/ |title=\u0d28\u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d24 \u0d31\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d4d\u200c\u0d38\u0d4d\u200c, Interview \u2013 Mathrubhumi Movies |publisher=Mathrubhumi.com |date=18 April 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024234532/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/354791/ |archivedate=24 October 2014  }}</ref> She was not trained in Mohiniyattam and learned the dance steps in [[Saranya Mohan]]'s dance school in [[Alappuzha]] for four days.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle1\"/> Both films were successful and she was selected as Top Star (Female) 2013 in Malayalam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themoviesdetails.blogspot.in/2014/01/top-10-highest-grossing-malayalam.html |title=The Movies Details/Reviews: TOP 10 HIGHEST GROSSING MALAYALAM MOVIES \u22122013 |publisher=Themoviesdetails.blogspot.in |date=9 January 2014 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, she was first seen in ''En Kadhal Pudhithu'', her debut Tamil film directed by Maaris Kumar which had a delayed release,<ref>[http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/130307/entertainment-kollywood/article/trailing-his-mentor Trailing his mentor | Deccan Chronicle]. Archives.deccanchronicle.com (7 March 2013). Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref> followed by Lijin Jose's ''[[Law Point]]'' in which she played a modern, city bred girl named Maya.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/malayalam/news-and-interviews/Namitha-going-glam/articleshow/27155306.cms |title=Namitha going glam \u2013 The Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=10 December 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mangalam.com/women/interview/16184 |title=\u0d28\u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d3e \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d2e\u0d4b\u0d26\u0d4d\u200c.. |publisher=mangalam.com |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> In [[Lal Jose]]'s ''[[Vikramadithyan]]'', she played the role of Deepika, a [[Konkani]] girl, which required her to speak a few lines in [[Konkani language|Konkani]], a language she had never used before. Her next film ''Villali Veeran'', in which she paired once again with Dileep, had her playing the role of an ad filmmaker.<ref>Nambidi, Parvathy. (26 June 2014) [http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/Veeran-Set-for-Onam-Arrival/2014/06/26/article2300320.ece 'Veeran' Set for Onam Arrival]. The New Indian Express. Retrieved on 14 October 2015.</ref> Her last release in 2014 was ''Ormayundo Ee Mukham'', a romantic drama in which she was cast opposite [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]].Her first release of 2015 was [[Chandrettan Evideya]] where she portrayed the role of Dr.Geethanjali along with [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]] and [[Anusree]].Her performance was critically acclaim and she went on to receive her first nomination at [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Malayalam|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress]]. Her next released Malayalam movie [[Amar Akbar Anthony (2015 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]] starring Prithviraj, Jayasurya and Indrajith directed by popular stage artist Nadirshah where she played a role as a dancer was a blockbuster hit in Malayalam theatres. Her latest movie with [[Dhyan Sreenivasan]] was [[Adi Kapyare Kootamani]] directed by debutant John Varghese.The movie was declared superhit.\n\nShe has acted in many [[commercials]] of [[Bhima Jewellers]], Francis Alukkas and Ripple Tea. She has participated in the popular [[reality show]] ''[[Ningalkkum Aakaam Kodeeshwaran]]'' on [[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Language\n!co-star\n! class=\"wikitable sortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Traffic (2011 film)|Traffic]]'' || Riya || [[Malayalam]] || [[Kunchako Boban]]||Debut\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]'' || Thamara || [[Malayalam]] || [[Nivin Pauly]]||\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2013 || ''[[Sound Thoma]]'' || Sreelakshmi || [[Malayalam]] || [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]]||\n|-\n| ''[[Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum]]'' || Kainakari Jayasree || [[Malayalam]] || [[Kunchako Boban]]||\n|-\n| rowspan=5| 2014 || ''En Kaadhal Pudhithu'' || Na