{"title_page": "Father of All Motherfuckers", "text_new": "{{Redirect|Father of All...|the album's title track|Father of All... (song)}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Father of All Motherfuckers\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Green Day]]\n| cover        = Father of All.jpg\n| alt          =\n| caption      = Standard edition album cover. The limited edition uses the same artwork but lacks the unicorn censoring \"motherfuckers\".\n| released     = {{Start date|2020|2|7}}\n| recorded     = June\u2013September 2019\n| studio       = \n| genre        = \n* [[Garage rock]]<ref name=\"rockcellarmagazine1\">{{cite web|last=Garro |first=Adrian |url=https://www.rockcellarmagazine.com/green-day-father-of-all-album-review-billie-joe-armstrong/ |title=Green Day: Still Full of 'Piss and Vinegar' on New Album 'Father of All ... ' - They Just Want You to Dance a Little Bit, Too (Review) |publisher=RockCellarMagazine |date= 6 February 2020|accessdate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n* [[alternative rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rocksins.com/2020/02/green-day-father-of-all-motherfuckers-38613/ |title=Green Day - Father Of All Motherfuckers |publisher=Rock Sins |date= 6 February 2020|accessdate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n* {{nowrap|[[Garage punk (fusion genre)|garage punk]]}}<ref name=\"rockcellarmagazine1\"/>\n* [[pop punk]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Beaumont |first=Mark |url=https://www.loudersound.com/features/green-day-have-made-a-college-jock-party-record-and-its-the-best-thing-theyve-done-in-years |title=Green Day - Father Of All Motherfuckers album review &#124; Louder |publisher=Loudersound.com |date= |accessdate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n| length       = 26:16<ref name=\"Daley 2019\">{{cite news |last1=Daley |first1=Rhian |title=Green Day's 2020 album 'Father Of All...' \u2013 tracklist, release date, artwork, and everything we know so far |url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/green-days-2020-album-father-of-all-motherfuckers-tracklist-release-date-artwork-tour-dates-2546723 |accessdate=September 13, 2019 |work=[[NME]] |date=September 13, 2019}}</ref>\n| label        = [[Reprise Records|Reprise]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Butch Walker]]|[[Chris Dugan]]|Green Day}}\n| prev_title   = [[Woodstock 1994 (Green Day album)|Woodstock 1994]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Green Day]] studio album\n | prev_title = [[Revolution Radio]]\n | prev_year  = 2016\n | title      = Father of All Motherfuckers \n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = Father of All Motherfuckers \n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Father of All... (song)|Father of All...]]\n | single1date = September 10, 2019\n | single2     = Fire, Ready, Aim\n | single2date = October 9, 2019\n | single3     = [[Oh Yeah! (Green Day song)|Oh Yeah!]]\n | single3date = January 16, 2020<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://thebuzz.iheart.com/featured/theresa/content/2020-02-07-green-day-dropped-the-video-for-new-single-meet-me-on-the-roof/|title=Green Day Dropped The Video For New Single 'Meet Me On The Roof' &#124; Theresa &#124; 94.5 The Buzz|website=Theresa}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://artesonora.pt/breves/green-day-ouve-o-novo-album-father-of-all-motherfuckers/|title=Green Day: Ouve o novo \u00e1lbum \"Father of All Motherfuckers\"|website=Arte Sonora}}</ref>\n | single4     = Meet Me on the Roof\n | single4date = February 7, 2020<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Father of All Motherfuckers''''' (also known by the censored form '''''Father of All...''''') is the thirteenth studio album by American [[Rock music|rock]] band [[Green Day]], released on February 7, 2020 through [[Reprise Records]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Green Day Announce New Album, Father Of All\u2026, And Stream Title-Track|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/green-day-announce-new-album-father-of-all-mother-fuckers-and-stream-title-track-1/|work=[[Kerrang!]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Trendell|first=Andrew|title=Green Day, Fall Out Boy and Weezer all drop new songs as they announce joint tour |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/green-day-weezer-fall-out-boy-joint-tour-new-songs-album-interview-tickets-2546517|work=[[NME]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref> It debuted atop the [[UK Albums Chart]] and Australian [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Albums Chart]], among others.\n\n==Composition==\nAccording to lead vocalist [[Billie Joe Armstrong]], the album is \"The New! [[soul music|soul]], [[Motown#Motown Sound|Motown]], [[glam rock|glam]] and manic anthemic. Punks, freaks and punishers!\" He would also state that the lyrics are about \"the life AND death of the party\" and the \"lifestyle of not giving a fuck.\"<ref name=\"Daley 2019\" /> With a running time of 26 minutes and 16 seconds, it is Green Day's shortest album.\n\nThe cover features the same image that features on the front of the band's 2004 LP ''[[American Idiot]]''. However, the arm holding the grenade is colored tan instead of white, and zoomed in. The full album title is written on the arm, with the word \"motherfuckers\" obscured by a unicorn drawing. The limited edition version of the album uses an alternate version of the cover, which lacks the unicorn.\n\n==Singles and promotion==\nThe album's [[lead single]] and title track, \"[[Father of All... (song)|Father of All...]]\", was released on September 10, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|author=Evan Minsker |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/green-day-announce-new-album-share-new-song-father-of-all-listen/ |title=Green Day Announce New Album, Share New Song \"Father of All...\": Listen |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date= |accessdate=2019-09-11}}</ref> A music video was released on September 19.<ref>{{cite web|author=Althea Legaspi |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/green-day-father-of-all-video-watch-887538/ |title=Green Day's New 'Father of All...' Video: Watch |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=2019-09-19 |accessdate=2020-02-05}}</ref> \"Fire, Ready, Aim\", was released on October 9 as the official opening theme song for the [[National Hockey League]] and [[NHL on NBC|NBCSN's]] [[Wednesday Night Rivalry|Wednesday Night Hockey]] television broadcasts and as the album's second single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://loudwire.com/green-day-fire-ready-aim-song-lyrics/ |title=Hear Green Day's Clap-Along New Song 'Fire, Ready, Aim' |publisher=Loudwire.com |date= |accessdate=2020-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/listen-to-green-days-new-single-fire-ready-aim/|title=Listen to Green Day's New Single, Fire, Ready, Aim|website=Kerrang!}}</ref> Coincidentally, NBCSN also uses \"Father of All...\", usually heard during highlights from previous games for the two teams playing on Wednesday Night Hockey.\n\nThe album's third single<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B8RN63igdMO/?igshid=gqg2vsqfyx1g|title=Butch Walker|last=|first=|date=|website=Instagram|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>, \"[[Oh Yeah! (Green Day song)|Oh Yeah!]]\", was released on January 16, 2020, along with a music video.<ref>(January 16, 2020). [https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/green-day-have-dropped-a-brand-new-song-oh-yeah/ \"Green Day Have Dropped A Brand-New Song, Oh Yeah!\"]. [[Kerrang!]]. Retrieved January 16, 2020.</ref> The song takes its title and samples the chorus from [[Joan Jett]]'s cover of \"[[Do You Wanna Touch Me]]\", originally sung by [[Gary Glitter]]. Acknowledging the latter's sexual abuse history and multiple convictions, the band mentioned they would donate their royalties from the sales of \"Oh Yeah!\" to [[International Justice Mission]] and [[Rape, Abuse & Incest National Network]].<ref>(January 16, 2020). [https://www.loudersound.com/news/green-day-launch-video-for-new-single-oh-yeah \"Green Day launch video for new single\"]. Louder Sound. Retrieved January 16, 2020.</ref>\n\nAt the same time as the album's release on digital platforms a music video for the song \"Meet Me on the Roof\" was released, featuring [[Gaten Matarazzo]] as a guest star. <ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/watch-stranger-things-dustin-in-the-new-green-day-video/|title=Watch Stranger Things' Dusting in the new Green Day video.|date=|work=Kerrang|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>  \n\nTo promote the album, the band is set to embark on the [[Hella Mega Tour]] with [[Fall Out Boy]] and [[Weezer]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Andy |last=Greene |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/green-day-weezer-fall-out-boy-2020-hella-mega-tour-882156/ |title=Green Day, Weezer, Fall Out Boy Announce 2020 'Hella Mega' Stadium Tour |work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 11, 2019}}</ref> Initially planned for March 2020, the tour is now set to begin in May 2020 following the delay of several shows in Asia.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Althea |last=Legaspi |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/green-day-postpone-asia-tour-coronavirus-959490/ |title=Green Day Postpone Asia Tour Dates Due to Coronavirus Concerns |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=February 28, 2020 |accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 6.1/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web |title=Father of All Motherfuckers by Green Day reviews |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/10244/Green-Day-Father-Of-All.aspx|accessdate=February 7, 2020 |website=[[AnyDecentMusic?]]}}</ref>\n| MC = 69/100<ref name=\"MC1\">{{cite web |title=Father of All Motherfuckers by Green Day Reviews and Tracks |url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/father-of-all/green-day|accessdate=February 7, 2020 |website=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/father-of-all%A6-mw0003318931|title=''Father of All...'' \u2013 Green Day|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|last=Thomas|first=Fred|authorlink=Fred Thomas (music critic)|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]''\n| rev2score = 7/10<ref name=\"Clash\">{{cite magazine|title=Green Day - Father Of All...|magazine=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/green-day-father-of-all|date=February 5, 2020|first=Nick|last=Roseblade|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"DIY\">{{cite magazine|title=Green Day - Father Of All...|magazine=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|url=https://diymag.com/2020/02/06/green-day-father-of-all-album-review|date=February 5, 2020|first=Sarah|last=Jamieson|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev4score = C\u2013<ref name=\"ew\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music-reviews/2020/02/06/green-days-father-of-all-ew-review/|title=Green Day's ''Father of All...'' plays like a copy of a copy|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Christopher R.|last=Weingarten|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev5score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=\"The Independent\">{{cite web|title=Green Day review, Father of All Motherf***ers: Onslaught of frenzied energy comes at the expense of innovation|website=[[The Independent]]|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/green-day-review-father-of-all-a9319456.html|date=February 6, 2020|first=Elisa|last=Bray|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Kerrang!]]''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"kerrang\">{{cite magazine|title=Green Day - Father of All... Review|magazine=[[Kerrang!]]|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-green-day-father-of-all/|date=February 5, 2020|first=Emily|last=Carter|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev7score = 6.7/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/green-day-father-of-all/|title=Green Day: Father of All... Album Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Rytlewski|first=Evan|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev8score = 5/10<ref name=\"PopMatters\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/green-day-father-of-all-2645028802.html|title=Green Day Struggle to Survive on 'Father of All'|website=[[PopMatters]]|first=Jordan|last=Blum|date=February 5, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev9score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/green-day-father-of-all-motherfuckers-review-948579/|title=Green Day Channel Classic Sounds They Love on 'Father of All\u2026'|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|first=Jon|last=Dolan|date=February 7, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]''\n| rev10score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"The Telegraph\">{{cite web|title=Green Day, Father of All..., review: it sounds like the Beatles being driven to homicide|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/green-day-father-review-sounds-like-beatles-driven-homicide/?wgu=275405_73669_15810211784048_4fcca01e87&wgexpiry=1588797178&WT.mc_id=tmgoff_paff-30828_subsoffers_basic_planit_us&utm_source=tmgoff&utm_medium=tmgoff_paff-30828&utm_content=subsoffers_basic&utm_campaign=tmgoff_paff-30828_subsoffers_basic_planit_us|date=February 6, 2020|first=Neil|last=McCormick|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Father of All Motherfuckers'' received polarized reviews from critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album has an average score of 69 out of 100, which indicates \"generally favorable reviews\" based on 22 reviews.<ref name=\"MC1\"/>\n\n''[[Kerrang!]]'' magazine rated the album four out of five stars, saying, \"''Father of All Motherfuckers'' is just another sign of a band who have always done things their way refusing to do what's expected of them. And it's a hella mega good time from start to finish\".<ref name=\"kerrang\"/> Reviewing for ''[[Rolling Stone (magazine)|Rolling Stone]]'', critic Jon Dolan also gave album four out of five stars, naming it one of Green Day's most fun albums, and writing, \"''Father of All...'' is a bountiful act of recovered rock memory, an effortlessly affirming argument that the first mosh pit or car radio contact high you get when you\u2019re 13 years old can be enough to sustain you long into life. <ref name=\"Rolling Stone\" /> Comparing it to their previous work, ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]'' magazine said, \"By its very nature, ''Father of All...'' is slight compared to a sprawling magnum opus such as 2009's ''[[21st Century Breakdown]]'', but it's close to impossible to emerge from its rapid-fire near-half-hour without a smile on your face.\"<ref name=\"q\">{{cite magazine|title=Let the Good Times Roll|magazine=[[Q (magazine)|Q]]|first=Andrew|last=Perry|date=March 2020|page=112}}</ref> \n\nConversely, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the album a middling C\u2013, saying, \"At its best, [''Father of All''] might be the dance party we need, but it's not the one we want.\"<ref name=\"ew\"/> More negatively, Ross Horton of ''[[musicOMH]]'' awarded it one out of five stars, calling it a disaster and pointing out that it is not a noble failure.<ref name=\"omh\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/green-day-father-of-all |work=[[musicOMH]] |title=Green Day&nbsp;\u2013 ''Father of All...'' |last=Horton |first=Ross |date=February 15, 2020 |accessdate=February 15, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Sputnikmusic]]'' gave the album a 1.5 out of 5 rating, calling the album \"a hot mess that destroys any hope that Green Day could re-emerge as a band worth listening to.\"<ref>[https://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/80849/Green-Day-Father-of-All-Motherfuckers/ sputnik]</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''Father of All Motherfuckers'' debuted at number four on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 48,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, including 42,000 pure album sales. It is Green Day's 11th US top-10 album.<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8551148/roddy-ricch-no-1-billboard-200-chart-fourth-week|title=Roddy Ricch Returns to No. 1 for Fourth Week on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=February 16, 2020|accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = [[Father of All... (song)|Father of All...]]\n| length1 = 2:31\n| title2 = Fire, Ready, Aim\n| length2 = 1:52\n| title3 = [[Oh Yeah! (Green Day song)|Oh Yeah!]]\n| length3 = 2:51\n| title4 = Meet Me on the Roof\n| length4 = 2:39\n| title5 = I Was a Teenage Teenager\n| length5 = 3:45\n| title6 = Stab You in the Heart\n| length6 = 2:10\n| title7 = Sugar Youth\n| length7 = 1:55\n| title8 = Junkies on a High\n| length8 = 3:06\n| title9 = Take the Money and Crawl\n| length9 = 2:09\n| title10 = Graffitia\n| length10 = 3:18\n| total_length = 26:16\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline  = Japanese edition<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://wmg.jp/greenday/discography/21802/ |title=Father of All... / \u30d5\u30a1\u30b6\u30fc\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30aa\u30fc\u30eb\u2026|publisher=Warner Music Japan |accessdate=February 12, 2020 }}</ref>\n| title11   = Bang Bang\n| note11    = live from the Wisky\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n===Green Day===\n* [[Billie Joe Armstrong]] \u2013 lead vocals, guitar, design\n* [[Mike Dirnt]] \u2013 bass guitar, background vocals\n* [[Tr\u00e9 Cool]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n===Production===\n*[[Butch Walker]] \u2013 production, engineering\n*[[Chris Dugan]] \u2013 production, mixing, engineering\n*Todd Stopera \u2013 assistant engineering\n*Tchad Blake \u2013 mixing\n*Elin B. \u2013 mixing assistant\n*Brian Lucey \u2013 mastering\n*Nathaniel Mela \u2013 drum tech\n*Andrew Hans Buscher \u2013 guitar tech\n*Chris Bilheimer \u2013 design\n*Pamela Littky \u2013 photography\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|1|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Austria|2|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|11|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|7|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|1|artist=Green Day|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Czech|59|date=202007|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|15|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 14, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonian Albums ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-ohoi-parim-uus-sooritaja-on-jaapanlane-joji?id=88955427|title=Eesti Tipp-40 Muusikas: Ohoi! Parim uus sooritaja on jaapanlane Joji!|language=Estonian|last=Nestor|first=Siim|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|date=February 18, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| 31\n|-\n{{album chart|Finland|14|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|France|34|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|2|id=394503|artist=Green Day|album=Father Of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Hungary|2|year=2020|week=7|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland3|4|date=20200214|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Italy|9|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Oricon|9|date=2020-02-17|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 12, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|New Zealand|9|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Norway|12|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Poland|28|id=1272|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Portugal|3|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|1|date=20200214|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Spain|7|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 19, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Sweden|19|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|1|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 19, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK2|1|date=20200214|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref name=\"BB200\"/>\n| 4\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|1|artist=Green Day|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 19, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 200|''Rolling Stone'' Top 200]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/albums/2020-02-13/|title=Top 200 Albums|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref>\n| 6\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Green Day}}\n\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Butch Walker]]\n[[Category:Green Day albums]]\n[[Category:Reprise Records albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Father of All...|the album's title track|Father of All... (song)}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Father of All Motherfuckers\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Green Day]]\n| cover        = Father of All.jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption      = Standard edition album cover. The limited edition uses the same artwork but lacks the unicorn censoring \"motherfuckers\".\n| released     = {{Start date|2020|2|7}}\n| recorded     = June\u2013September 2019\n| studio       = \n| genre        = \n* [[Garage rock]]<ref name=\"rockcellarmagazine1\">{{cite web|last=Garro |first=Adrian |url=https://www.rockcellarmagazine.com/green-day-father-of-all-album-review-billie-joe-armstrong/ |title=Green Day: Still Full of 'Piss and Vinegar' on New Album 'Father of All ... ' - They Just Want You to Dance a Little Bit, Too (Review) |publisher=RockCellarMagazine |date= 6 February 2020|accessdate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n* [[alternative rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rocksins.com/2020/02/green-day-father-of-all-motherfuckers-38613/ |title=Green Day - Father Of All Motherfuckers |publisher=Rock Sins |date= 6 February 2020|accessdate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n* {{nowrap|[[Garage punk (fusion genre)|garage punk]]}}<ref name=\"rockcellarmagazine1\"/>\n* [[pop punk]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Beaumont |first=Mark |url=https://www.loudersound.com/features/green-day-have-made-a-college-jock-party-record-and-its-the-best-thing-theyve-done-in-years |title=Green Day - Father Of All Motherfuckers album review &#124; Louder |publisher=Loudersound.com |date= |accessdate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n| length       = 26:16<ref name=\"Daley 2019\">{{cite news |last1=Daley |first1=Rhian |title=Green Day's 2020 album 'Father Of All...' \u2013 tracklist, release date, artwork, and everything we know so far |url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/green-days-2020-album-father-of-all-motherfuckers-tracklist-release-date-artwork-tour-dates-2546723 |accessdate=September 13, 2019 |work=[[NME]] |date=September 13, 2019}}</ref>\n| label        = [[Reprise Records|Reprise]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Butch Walker]]|[[Chris Dugan]]|Green Day}}\n| prev_title   = [[Woodstock 1994 (Green Day album)|Woodstock 1994]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Green Day]] studio album\n | prev_title = [[Revolution Radio]]\n | prev_year  = 2016\n | title      = Father of All Motherfuckers \n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = Father of All Motherfuckers \n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Father of All... (song)|Father of All...]]\n | single1date = September 10, 2019\n | single2     = Fire, Ready, Aim\n | single2date = October 9, 2019\n | single3     = [[Oh Yeah! (Green Day song)|Oh Yeah!]]\n | single3date = January 16, 2020<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://thebuzz.iheart.com/featured/theresa/content/2020-02-07-green-day-dropped-the-video-for-new-single-meet-me-on-the-roof/|title=Green Day Dropped The Video For New Single 'Meet Me On The Roof' &#124; Theresa &#124; 94.5 The Buzz|website=Theresa}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://artesonora.pt/breves/green-day-ouve-o-novo-album-father-of-all-motherfuckers/|title=Green Day: Ouve o novo \u00e1lbum \"Father of All Motherfuckers\"|website=Arte Sonora}}</ref>\n | single4     = Meet Me on the Roof\n | single4date = February 7, 2020<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Father of All Motherfuckers''''' (also known by the censored form '''''Father of All...''''') is the thirteenth studio album by American [[Rock music|rock]] band [[Green Day]], released on February 7, 2020 through [[Reprise Records]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Green Day Announce New Album, Father Of All\u2026, And Stream Title-Track|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/green-day-announce-new-album-father-of-all-mother-fuckers-and-stream-title-track-1/|work=[[Kerrang!]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Trendell|first=Andrew|title=Green Day, Fall Out Boy and Weezer all drop new songs as they announce joint tour |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/green-day-weezer-fall-out-boy-joint-tour-new-songs-album-interview-tickets-2546517|work=[[NME]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref> It debuted atop the [[UK Albums Chart]] and Australian [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Albums Chart]], among others.\n\n==Composition==\nAccording to lead vocalist [[Billie Joe Armstrong]], the album is \"The New! [[soul music|soul]], [[Motown#Motown Sound|Motown]], [[glam rock|glam]] and manic anthemic. Punks, freaks and punishers!\" He would also state that the lyrics are about \"the life AND death of the party\" and the \"lifestyle of not giving a fuck.\"<ref name=\"Daley 2019\" /> With a running time of 26 minutes and 16 seconds, it is Green Day's shortest album.\n\nThe cover features the same image that features on the front of the band's 2004 LP ''[[American Idiot]]''. However, the arm holding the grenade is colored tan instead of white, and zoomed in. The full album title is written on the arm, with the word \"motherfuckers\" obscured by a unicorn drawing. The limited edition version of the album uses an alternate version of the cover, which lacks the unicorn.\n\n==Singles and promotion==\nThe album's [[lead single]] and title track, \"[[Father of All... (song)|Father of All...]]\", was released on September 10, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|author=Evan Minsker |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/green-day-announce-new-album-share-new-song-father-of-all-listen/ |title=Green Day Announce New Album, Share New Song \"Father of All...\": Listen |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date= |accessdate=2019-09-11}}</ref> A music video was released on September 19.<ref>{{cite web|author=Althea Legaspi |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/green-day-father-of-all-video-watch-887538/ |title=Green Day's New 'Father of All...' Video: Watch |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=2019-09-19 |accessdate=2020-02-05}}</ref> \"Fire, Ready, Aim\", was released on October 9 as the official opening theme song for the [[National Hockey League]] and [[NHL on NBC|NBCSN's]] [[Wednesday Night Rivalry|Wednesday Night Hockey]] television broadcasts and as the album's second single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://loudwire.com/green-day-fire-ready-aim-song-lyrics/ |title=Hear Green Day's Clap-Along New Song 'Fire, Ready, Aim' |publisher=Loudwire.com |date= |accessdate=2020-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/listen-to-green-days-new-single-fire-ready-aim/|title=Listen to Green Day's New Single, Fire, Ready, Aim|website=Kerrang!}}</ref> Coincidentally, NBCSN also uses \"Father of All...\", usually heard during highlights from previous games for the two teams playing on Wednesday Night Hockey.\n\nThe album's third single<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B8RN63igdMO/?igshid=gqg2vsqfyx1g|title=Butch Walker|last=|first=|date=|website=Instagram|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>, \"[[Oh Yeah! (Green Day song)|Oh Yeah!]]\", was released on January 16, 2020, along with a music video.<ref>(January 16, 2020). [https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/green-day-have-dropped-a-brand-new-song-oh-yeah/ \"Green Day Have Dropped A Brand-New Song, Oh Yeah!\"]. [[Kerrang!]]. Retrieved January 16, 2020.</ref> The song takes its title and samples the chorus from [[Joan Jett]]'s cover of \"[[Do You Wanna Touch Me]]\", originally sung by [[Gary Glitter]]. Acknowledging the latter's sexual abuse history and multiple convictions, the band mentioned they would donate their royalties from the sales of \"Oh Yeah!\" to [[International Justice Mission]] and [[Rape, Abuse & Incest National Network]].<ref>(January 16, 2020). [https://www.loudersound.com/news/green-day-launch-video-for-new-single-oh-yeah \"Green Day launch video for new single\"]. Louder Sound. Retrieved January 16, 2020.</ref>\n\nAt the same time as the album's release on digital platforms a music video for the song \"Meet Me on the Roof\" was released, featuring [[Gaten Matarazzo]] as a guest star. <ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/watch-stranger-things-dustin-in-the-new-green-day-video/|title=Watch Stranger Things' Dusting in the new Green Day video.|date=|work=Kerrang|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>  \n\nTo promote the album, the band is set to embark on the [[Hella Mega Tour]] with [[Fall Out Boy]] and [[Weezer]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Andy |last=Greene |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/green-day-weezer-fall-out-boy-2020-hella-mega-tour-882156/ |title=Green Day, Weezer, Fall Out Boy Announce 2020 'Hella Mega' Stadium Tour |work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 11, 2019}}</ref> Initially planned for March 2020, the tour is now set to begin in May 2020 following the delay of several shows in Asia.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Althea |last=Legaspi |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/green-day-postpone-asia-tour-coronavirus-959490/ |title=Green Day Postpone Asia Tour Dates Due to Coronavirus Concerns |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=February 28, 2020 |accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 6.1/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web |title=Father of All Motherfuckers by Green Day reviews |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/10244/Green-Day-Father-Of-All.aspx|accessdate=February 7, 2020 |website=[[AnyDecentMusic?]]}}</ref>\n| MC = 69/100<ref name=\"MC1\">{{cite web |title=Father of All Motherfuckers by Green Day Reviews and Tracks |url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/father-of-all/green-day|accessdate=February 7, 2020 |website=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/father-of-all%A6-mw0003318931|title=''Father of All...'' \u2013 Green Day|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|last=Thomas|first=Fred|authorlink=Fred Thomas (music critic)|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]''\n| rev2score = 7/10<ref name=\"Clash\">{{cite magazine|title=Green Day - Father Of All...|magazine=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/green-day-father-of-all|date=February 5, 2020|first=Nick|last=Roseblade|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"DIY\">{{cite magazine|title=Green Day - Father Of All...|magazine=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|url=https://diymag.com/2020/02/06/green-day-father-of-all-album-review|date=February 5, 2020|first=Sarah|last=Jamieson|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev4score = C\u2013<ref name=\"ew\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music-reviews/2020/02/06/green-days-father-of-all-ew-review/|title=Green Day's ''Father of All...'' plays like a copy of a copy|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Christopher R.|last=Weingarten|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev5score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=\"The Independent\">{{cite web|title=Green Day review, Father of All Motherf***ers: Onslaught of frenzied energy comes at the expense of innovation|website=[[The Independent]]|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/green-day-review-father-of-all-a9319456.html|date=February 6, 2020|first=Elisa|last=Bray|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Kerrang!]]''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"kerrang\">{{cite magazine|title=Green Day - Father of All... Review|magazine=[[Kerrang!]]|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-green-day-father-of-all/|date=February 5, 2020|first=Emily|last=Carter|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev7score = 6.7/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/green-day-father-of-all/|title=Green Day: Father of All... Album Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Rytlewski|first=Evan|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev8score = 5/10<ref name=\"PopMatters\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/green-day-father-of-all-2645028802.html|title=Green Day Struggle to Survive on 'Father of All'|website=[[PopMatters]]|first=Jordan|last=Blum|date=February 5, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev9score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/green-day-father-of-all-motherfuckers-review-948579/|title=Green Day Channel Classic Sounds They Love on 'Father of All\u2026'|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|first=Jon|last=Dolan|date=February 7, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]''\n| rev10score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"The Telegraph\">{{cite web|title=Green Day, Father of All..., review: it sounds like the Beatles being driven to homicide|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/green-day-father-review-sounds-like-beatles-driven-homicide/?wgu=275405_73669_15810211784048_4fcca01e87&wgexpiry=1588797178&WT.mc_id=tmgoff_paff-30828_subsoffers_basic_planit_us&utm_source=tmgoff&utm_medium=tmgoff_paff-30828&utm_content=subsoffers_basic&utm_campaign=tmgoff_paff-30828_subsoffers_basic_planit_us|date=February 6, 2020|first=Neil|last=McCormick|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Father of All Motherfuckers'' received polarized reviews from critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album has an average score of 69 out of 100, which indicates \"generally favorable reviews\" based on 22 reviews.<ref name=\"MC1\"/>\n\n''[[Kerrang!]]'' magazine rated the album four out of five stars, saying, \"''Father of All Motherfuckers'' is just another sign of a band who have always done things their way refusing to do what's expected of them. And it's a hella mega good time from start to finish\".<ref name=\"kerrang\"/> Reviewing for ''[[Rolling Stone (magazine)|Rolling Stone]]'', critic Jon Dolan also gave album four out of five stars, naming it one of Green Day's most fun albums, and writing, \"''Father of All...'' is a bountiful act of recovered rock memory, an effortlessly affirming argument that the first mosh pit or car radio contact high you get when you\u2019re 13 years old can be enough to sustain you long into life. <ref name=\"Rolling Stone\" /> Comparing it to their previous work, ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]'' magazine said, \"By its very nature, ''Father of All...'' is slight compared to a sprawling magnum opus such as 2009's ''[[21st Century Breakdown]]'', but it's close to impossible to emerge from its rapid-fire near-half-hour without a smile on your face.\"<ref name=\"q\">{{cite magazine|title=Let the Good Times Roll|magazine=[[Q (magazine)|Q]]|first=Andrew|last=Perry|date=March 2020|page=112}}</ref> \n\nConversely, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the album a middling C\u2013, saying, \"At its best, [''Father of All''] might be the dance party we need, but it's not the one we want.\"<ref name=\"ew\"/> More negatively, Ross Horton of ''[[musicOMH]]'' awarded it one out of five stars, calling it a disaster and pointing out that it is not a noble failure.<ref name=\"omh\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/green-day-father-of-all |work=[[musicOMH]] |title=Green Day&nbsp;\u2013 ''Father of All...'' |last=Horton |first=Ross |date=February 15, 2020 |accessdate=February 15, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Sputnikmusic]]'' gave the album a 1.5 out of 5 rating, calling the album \"a hot mess that destroys any hope that Green Day could re-emerge as a band worth listening to.\"<ref>[https://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/80849/Green-Day-Father-of-All-Motherfuckers/ sputnik]</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''Father of All Motherfuckers'' debuted at number four on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 48,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, including 42,000 pure album sales. It is Green Day's 11th US top-10 album.<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8551148/roddy-ricch-no-1-billboard-200-chart-fourth-week|title=Roddy Ricch Returns to No. 1 for Fourth Week on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=February 16, 2020|accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = [[Father of All... (song)|Father of All...]]\n| length1 = 2:31\n| title2 = Fire, Ready, Aim\n| length2 = 1:52\n| title3 = [[Oh Yeah! (Green Day song)|Oh Yeah!]]\n| length3 = 2:51\n| title4 = Meet Me on the Roof\n| length4 = 2:39\n| title5 = I Was a Teenage Teenager\n| length5 = 3:45\n| title6 = Stab You in the Heart\n| length6 = 2:10\n| title7 = Sugar Youth\n| length7 = 1:55\n| title8 = Junkies on a High\n| length8 = 3:06\n| title9 = Take the Money and Crawl\n| length9 = 2:09\n| title10 = Graffitia\n| length10 = 3:18\n| total_length = 26:16\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline  = Japanese edition<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://wmg.jp/greenday/discography/21802/ |title=Father of All... / \u30d5\u30a1\u30b6\u30fc\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30aa\u30fc\u30eb\u2026|publisher=Warner Music Japan |accessdate=February 12, 2020 }}</ref>\n| title11   = Bang Bang\n| note11    = live from the Wisky\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n===Green Day===\n* [[Billie Joe Armstrong]] \u2013 lead vocals, guitar, design\n* [[Mike Dirnt]] \u2013 bass guitar, background vocals\n* [[Tr\u00e9 Cool]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n===Production===\n*[[Butch Walker]] \u2013 production, engineering\n*[[Chris Dugan]] \u2013 production, mixing, engineering\n*Todd Stopera \u2013 assistant engineering\n*Tchad Blake \u2013 mixing\n*Elin B. \u2013 mixing assistant\n*Brian Lucey \u2013 mastering\n*Nathaniel Mela \u2013 drum tech\n*Andrew Hans Buscher \u2013 guitar tech\n*Chris Bilheimer \u2013 design\n*Pamela Littky \u2013 photography\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|1|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Austria|2|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|11|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|7|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|1|artist=Green Day|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Czech|59|date=202007|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|15|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 14, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonian Albums ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-ohoi-parim-uus-sooritaja-on-jaapanlane-joji?id=88955427|title=Eesti Tipp-40 Muusikas: Ohoi! Parim uus sooritaja on jaapanlane Joji!|language=Estonian|last=Nestor|first=Siim|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|date=February 18, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| 31\n|-\n{{album chart|Finland|14|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|France|34|artist=Green Day|album=Father of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|2|id=394503|artist=Green Day|album=Father Of All...|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Hungary|2|year=2020|week=7|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland3|4|date=20200214|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Italy|9|artist=Green Day|al