{"title_page": "List of Nairs", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\nThis '''list of Notable Nairs''' contains some notable members of the [[Nair]] community of southern India.\n\n==Dynasties==\n\n* [[Kingdom of Travancore]]\n* [[Zamorin of Calicut]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xu-O9eNmQXMC&pg=PT162 |title=Land of seven rivers: History of India's Geography |author=Sanjeev Sanyal |website=Books.google.com |year=2012}}</ref>\n* [[Chirakkal Raja]]<ref name=\"google2\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hkbJ6xA1_jEC&pg=PA140 |title=History of Tipu Sultan |author=Mohibbul Hasan |page=140 |year= }}</ref>\n* [[Kadathanadu]]<ref name=\"google2\"/>\n* [[Kingdom of Kottayam]]<ref name=\"google2\"/>\n* [[Venad|Kingdom of Venad]]<ref name=\"gough\">{{Cite book|title=Matrilineal Kinship|editor1-first=David Murray |editor1-last=Schneider |editor2-first=Kathleen |editor2-last=Gough |last=Gough|first=Kathleen |authorlink=Kathleen Gough |chapter=Central Kerala|publisher=University of California Press|year=1962|isbn=978-1111665906|pages=303-304}}</ref> \n* [[Valluvanad (southern Malabar)|Valluvanad]]<ref name=\"gough\" />\n* [[Ern\u0101d]]<ref name=\"gough\" />\n* [[Palakkad district|Palakkad]]<ref name=\"gough\" />\n* [[Kolathunadu|Kingdom of Kolathunadu]]<ref name=\"gough\" />\n* [[Paliath Achan|Paliyath Swaroopam]]\n* [[Nilambur Kingdom]]\n*[[Kingdom of Tanur]]\n\n==Spiritual leaders==\n* [[Tapovan Maharaj]]<ref>{{cite book |last= Chinmayananda |first=  |date= |title=Journey Of A Master |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LVFgGKeAzFUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Journey+Of+A+Master&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjw9MHvopbKAhUF6SYKHa5wBusQ6AEIJTAA#v=onepage&q=Journey%20Of%20A%20Master&f=false|website=Books.google.com  |page= 79|}}</ref>\n* [[Chattampi Swamikal]]<ref name=\"Nangelimalil1996\">{{cite book|author=Jacob Nangelimalil|title=The Relationship Between the Eucharistic Liturgy, the Interior